    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "deviceClass": "Class II"
  },
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/noncannulated-fea-credibility-claim-001",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA model ensemble is credible for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending QoIs of non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct",
      "description": "The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes implementations) is asserted to be sufficiently credible for predicting construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading conditions. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; 12 of 13 meet or exceed required levels. The single sub-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved=1, required=2) is accepted under risk-informed rationale given the well-controlled laboratory environment and cross-laboratory reproducibility. The model ensemble is therefore suitable to support the regulatory submission decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw design.",
      "scope": "Non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw, ASTM F1717 static compression-bending, construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement",
      "purpose": "Support FDA 510(k) regulatory decision for Class II spinal implant device"
    }
  ],
