      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residuals must converge to < 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error < 0.1%.",
      "rationale": "All 33 simulation runs (3 QoIs × 11 virtual constructs) converged to force residual < 1e-7 and moment residual < 1e-7. Energy balance error < 0.05% across all runs. No non-convergence events recorded."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments by a qualified simulation engineer not involved in primary analysis.",
      "rationale": "Independent peer review conducted by senior FEA engineer (10+ years orthopedic implant simulation experience). Review checklist covered geometry import, contact definitions, material assignments, boundary conditions, and load application. Two minor discrepancies identified and corrected prior to final runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model must capture elastic-plastic behavior of titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) with documented justification; contact formulation must be appropriate for screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model used for Ti-6Al-4V (E=114 GPa, yield=880 MPa, tangent modulus=1.2 GPa) based on coupon tensile testing from the same material lot. Augmented Lagrange contact formulation with friction coefficient 0.25 (measured by tribology testing). Model form consistent with published literature for pedicle screw FEA."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties, geometry, and boundary conditions must be derived from measured values with documented uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "All geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production hardware (n=5 screws, n=5 rods). Material properties from coupon testing (n=10 tensile specimens per lot). Uncertainty propagation performed via Monte Carlo simulation (10,000 samples). 95th percentile prediction intervals reported for all QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental constructs must use production-representative hardware; sample size must support statistical comparison (N ≥ 5 per laboratory).",
      "rationale": "N=6 constructs tested at Laboratory 1 and N=5 at Laboratory 2, all assembled from production-lot hardware (same lot as clinical devices). Construct assembly performed by trained technicians following ASTM F1717 protocol. Hardware dimensions verified by CMM prior to testing."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must cover at least two clinically relevant loading scenarios or loading rates to assess model sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single loading condition (quasi-static, 5 mm/min displacement rate) per ASTM F1717. Dynamic or fatigue loading not included in this validation activity. Achieved level 1 is below required level 2; accepted under risk-informed rationale given that the regulatory submission is limited to static performance claims and the single condition is well-controlled and reproducible across both laboratories."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model input parameters must be traceable to the same hardware lot and material certificates as the experimental test articles.",
      "rationale": "Full traceability established between FEA inputs and experimental test articles: same material lot (certificate of conformance on file), same nominal geometry (CMM reports cross-referenced), same torque specification for screw-rod locking (4 Nm per surgical technique guide). Traceability matrix documented in report TM-2023-F1717-001."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval must be reported for all QoIs; relative difference must be < 10%.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for all three QoIs across both laboratories: stiffness (Lab1: 0.71, Lab2: 0.59), yield force (Lab1: 0.61, Lab2: 0.68), force at 40 mm (Lab1: 0.65, Lab2: 0.72). All values below 1.96. Maximum relative difference 2.85%. Bayesian credible intervals also reported. Achieved level 4 reflects comprehensive statistical treatment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
