      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) must be directly relevant to the clinical and regulatory decision.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load-sharing with the spine; yield force is a direct failure metric; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue initiation. All three QoIs are specified in FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions and are directly linked to the COU decision consequence assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
